alid JSON object with these EXACT fields:\n  * "action": "update_school" (always this exact string)\n  * "school_id": The UUID of the school (e.g., "ee8981ae-7f29-47bf-968c-4829381e0559")\n  * "data": An object containing ONLY the fields that need to be updated\n- The JSON must be properly formatted with double quotes around all keys and string values - Do NOT use single quotes or unquoted keys in the JSON - Example of CORRECT format:\n  ```\n  Action: supabase_tool\n  Action Input: {"action": "update_school", "school_id": "ee8981ae-7f29-47bf-968c-4829381e0559", "data": {"total_student_enrollment": 115, "latitude": 35.153045, "longitude": -92.740309}}\n  ```\n\nDATA VALIDATION REQUIREMENTS: - Validate all data before updating:\n  * total_student_enrollment should be a positive integer (typically between 10 and 5000)\n  * latitude should be between 24 and 50 (continental US)\n  * longitude should be between -125 and -65 (continental US)\n  * phone numbers should be in format (XXX) XXX-XXXX if present\n- Skip updating any field with invalid data and note it in your report\nIMPORTANT: You will receive the schools data from the previous tasks. You should use this data to update the database. DO NOT make up random school IDs or data. Use ONLY the schools and data provided in the task context.\nEXAMPLE TASK CONTEXT STRUCTURE: ``` {\n  "data": {\n    "schools": [\n      {\n        "school_id": "ee8981ae-7f29-47bf-968c-4829381e0559",\n        "school_name": "SACRED HEART CATHOLIC HIGH SCHOOL",\n        ...\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  "previous_task_output": [\n    {\n      "school_id": "ee8981ae-7f29-47bf-968c-4829381e0559",\n      "enriched_fields": {\n        "latitude": 35.153045,\n        "longitude": -92.740309\n      },\n      "status": "success"\n    }\n  ],\n  "task_history": [\n    {\n      "task": "research_task",\n      "output": [...]\n    },\n    {\n      "task": "scraping_task",\n      "output": [...]\n    },\n    {\n      "task": "geocoding_task",\n      "output